        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 1 at 4:16PM EDT until August 1 at 5:00PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Mocksville,
moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Mocksville, Bermuda Run, Advance, and Fork Church.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
